 <h2>GoD: Soloing in Natambi</h2><br><br>Natambi is a fairly good solo zone for mages, thanks to <i>Izzadan</i> of Rodcet Nife for contributing this mob list. These were written from the perspective of a level61 mage using WoX pet.</center><br><br>1) <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14223">A Hynid Fleshripper</a> - Very easy to be soloed by me. i would say max hit for them is 235 to 170 ish and have about 7-8k hps. (they tend to take 61 pet down to about half health with one TER thrown in).<br><br>2) <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14491">A Feirce Cragwalker</a> - Be warned, do not attempt with out a slower (<i>Or Planar Renewal - Ed</i>), i had to chain cast about 4 air pets (61 air pet) and eventually killed him. Nice loot as well, a 3int spell haste 3 item on him. (Same goes for a furious)<br><br>3) <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14222">A Turepta Cragwalker</a> - Also easy to solo, max hit about 180, though doubles for 175 most of the time.<br><br>4) <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14225">A Noc Darklurch</a> - Bad, i couldnt solo these as they hit for about 250ish and have a mean 550 DD proc that goes off A LOT. I did however duo with a 62 shaman and we owned these suckers real easy.<br><br>5) We also popped <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14229">Kyv Heartpeircer</a> (named arrow guy) a few times while fighting there. Max hit about 520ish, same proc as most of the other mobs in zone. He fires arrows that can either snare you, drain your mana, and i forgot the other proc. He wasnt to tough of a fight for me and the 62 shammy, once slowed he he was as good as erudite MEAT. 61 AIR pet tanked him very well. It was buffed by the shammy and healed about 4 times in fight by him, I also threw in about 6 TER heals for my pet. Once he is below 40%, nuke him and he will die real fast. He dropped a nice sword that sells for about 10-12k.<br><br>6) <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14226">A Restless Soul</a> - Mobs at the ruins accross the river from camp, these aren't so easy. They can tear my pet apart in lil over 20 seconds. I've not tried nuking 'em to death though. They hit for about 240 ish and have a proc.<br><br>Well thats it from me for now, oh and  remember, dont aggro the <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14213">Cragbeast Queen</a>, she hits hard (4k) and runs very fast!<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(237); return false;'>Natimbi - The Broken Shores mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(237); return false;'>Natimbi - The Broken Shores quest list</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>izzadan</b> says:</i><br>please, if anybody has comment/feedback or would like to update sometihng go rigt ahead, im listing. 

thnx<br><br><i><b>Fayline Fyrecat</b> says:</i><br>Good start Izz, and thanks.  One thing I would like to add is in regards to the underwater spawns.  I soloed from 59.2 to 60 in this zone, and since the turtles (turepta) and shore stonemites are on a relatively slow timer, I would summon up a water stone and head below in the straight in front of the camp.  There are about 6 to 8 static spawns of crustaceans, swordfish, and squid (I'm at work, mob names escape me atm).  All underwater spawns, turtles, hynids, and stonemites are in the DB/LB range at 59-60, and I was getting 1% reg exp per 3 kills at 59; and just under double that amount at 60.  The turtles and crustaceans (normal mobs) have been known to drop a FT neck piece and a melee equivalent Aura of Courage(?) piece, the latter I was lucky enough to loot myself.  Last tidbit of info; fishing is a worthwhile past-time while medding, as the fish/crabs you catch sell for an average of 2pp each depending on their weight.  Enjoy!

